        "A young woman with long auburn hair swept over one shoulder stands in a sun-drenched greenhouse, wearing a fitted olive linen apron over a cream ribbed tank top, her sleeves pushed up past her elbows revealing freckled forearms dusted with potting soil. Her green-hazel eyes catch the warm diffused light filtering through fogged glass panes overhead as she holds a small terracotta pot in one hand and a brass misting bottle in the other, head tilted slightly with a soft closed-lip smile. Hanging plants cascade around her in trailing vines of pothos and string-of-pearls, and wooden shelves behind her overflow with succulents, ceramic pots, and glass propagation jars filled with cuttings in clear water. Golden hour light pours through the humid glass in soft shafts, catching suspended dust motes and tiny water droplets in the air, casting warm honeyed shadows across her collarbones and the bridge of her nose where a faint band of freckles crosses from cheek to cheek. A black cat sits on the potting bench beside her, one paw raised mid-groom, partially obscured by a sprawling monstera leaf. Shot on a 50mm lens at f1.4, shallow depth of field, warm color grade with lifted shadows and soft green tones throughout."
